We are given an unknown polynomial <i>f</i> ∈ ℤ[<i>x</i>] by a black box which on input <i>a</i> ∈ ℤ returns a value <i>r</i><inf><i>q</i></inf> · <i>f</i>(<i>a</i>) for some unknown nonzero rational numbers <i>r</i><inf><i>a</i></inf>. If we have appropriate upper bounds on the numerator and denominator of <i>r</i><inf><i>a</i></inf> and the degree of <i>f</i>, then the coefficients of <i>f</i> can be computed in probabilistic polynomial time.